Package edu.wit.scds.comp2000.queue

Interface QueueInterface<T>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of all objects to store in the queue
All Known Implementing Classes:
ArrayQueue
public interface QueueInterface<T>
An interface for the ADT queue.
Version:
5.0, 5.1.0 2019-07-14 minor revisions per Dave Rosenberg Company coding standard and class assignment, 5.2.0 2020-03-01 update to coding standard
Author:
Frank M. Carrano, Timothy M. Henry, David M Rosenberg

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void clear()
    Removes all entries from this queue.
    T dequeue()
    Removes and returns the entry at the front of this queue.
    void enqueue​(T newEntry)
    Adds a new entry to the back of this queue.
    T getFront()
    Retrieves the entry at the front of this queue.
    boolean isEmpty()
    Detects whether this queue is empty.

  • Method Details

    • clear

      void clear()
      Removes all entries from this queue.

    • dequeue

      T dequeue()
      Removes and returns the entry at the front of this queue.
      Returns:
      The object at the front of the queue.
      Throws:
      EmptyQueueException - if the queue is empty before the operation.

    • enqueue

      void enqueue​(T newEntry)
      Adds a new entry to the back of this queue.
      Parameters:
      newEntry - An object to be added.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the queue can't grow to accept the new entry

    • getFront

      T getFront()
      Retrieves the entry at the front of this queue.
      Returns:
      The object at the front of the queue.
      Throws:
      EmptyQueueException - if the queue is empty.

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Detects whether this queue is empty.
      Returns:
      True if the queue is empty, or false otherwise.
